children.content: This is an “Activity”. It is something to be done as part of the project. It can be automatic or manual. It can be simple or very complex, like a long process But, in summary, it´s just something that must be done

This is an Aggregate. An Aggregation is a collection of Information and functionality with very clear meaning for the business
In this example, the Aggregate "Customer" will provide most or all the needed Information and Functionality to complete the Activity
The Aggregate may use other aggregation to provide the functionality, but this is transparent for the business activity
Each Aggregate have a single IT Owner in IT organization(s) (it may have one in Architecture and one in Development and one in operations, but never 2 in Architecture or 2 in Development or 2 in Operations)
Each Aggregate have a single Business Owner
Each Aggregatee will have one or several Domain Experts (the guys that knows and can explain well the business to the IT)
The Information provided by an aggregated is structured in Entities. For example, the customer aggregate can provide Customer Credit Rating information of the customer, or the customer positions
